author: Russell Brand
description:
Palantir sounds like a sci-fi villain, but this isn’t fiction—this is real. In this episode of Unpacked, I take a deep dive into how this CIA-backed tech giant has quietly become the backbone of US surveillance infrastructure—under both Biden and Trump. From migrant tracking to medical and financial profiling, they’re centralizing everything. But it gets darker: their CEO openly talks about setting a “global standard for behavior.” That’s not tech—it’s tyranny. Let's unpack what this means for freedom, privacy, and the illusion of political difference.
